replies.bodyText:
we want to use the new API, and only the new API, everywhere it is possible.

That was my first thought as well. It was something like
if (SET_APPLICATION_PROTOCOLS.isSupported(sslParams)) {
  // invoke SET_APPLICATION_PROTOCOLS on sslParams and sslSocket.setSSLParameters(sslParams)
} else {
  // invoke SET_ALPN_PROTOCOLS/SET_NPN_PROTOCOLS
}

However, when using bundled Conscrypt (i.e., org.conscrypt) on Android Q+, this doesn't work. We would still need to invoke SET_ALPN_PROTOCOLS/SET_NPN_PROTOCOLS.

